WEBVTT

00:00.750 --> 00:01.583
Three guys, three stiffs.

00:01.667 --> 00:03.333
According to the cops,
that's it.

00:03.542 --> 00:04.959
PERRY MASON:
Except we know there's a fourth.

00:05.542 --> 00:07.000
Get a little help
at the crime scene?

00:07.083 --> 00:08.917
I got no idea
what you're talking about.

00:10.583 --> 00:11.750
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:12.000 --> 00:14.959
Heard about Perry Mason sniffing
around those shootings.

00:15.041 --> 00:15.917
Don't talk to him.

00:16.291 --> 00:18.625
If any of this comes back to me
I will deny every word.

00:19.125 --> 00:21.625
PETE STRICKLAND:
Ennis cut the line
to be first at Angel's Flight.

00:22.041 --> 00:24.959
Then, he's at Gannon's almost
before the call went out.

00:25.041 --> 00:27.208
MASON:
You think he's sitting nearby
to control the crime scenes?

00:27.834 --> 00:29.166
STRICKLAND:
It's quite the co-inky-dink.

00:29.667 --> 00:32.542
Charlie Dodson will rise again!

00:33.000 --> 00:35.375
WOMAN: If you truly believe
God told you to do this,

00:35.625 --> 00:37.583
tell him, "Don't let me down."

00:37.917 --> 00:39.417
You think I want God in my head?

00:39.750 --> 00:41.917
No one wants this case, Emily.

00:42.917 --> 00:44.458
You need new representation.

00:44.750 --> 00:45.583
But he's not a lawyer.

00:45.959 --> 00:48.375
There's a bar examination
which will certify him

00:48.458 --> 00:49.458
with plenty of time.

00:49.667 --> 00:50.792
I will prove your innocence.

00:52.583 --> 00:53.834
So help me God.

00:54.208 --> 00:55.333
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:03.083 --> 01:06.208
MAYNARD BARNES:
The defendant, Emily Dodson,

01:06.291 --> 01:09.750
was the only person
who had the means,

01:09.834 --> 01:13.208
motive, and opportunity

01:13.291 --> 01:16.083
to orchestrate
this despicable plan.

01:16.166 --> 01:19.959
Now, Emily Dodson knew

01:20.041 --> 01:23.291
that her husband was the son
of a very wealthy man,

01:23.375 --> 01:26.667
and therefore, someone
with means to obtain

01:26.750 --> 01:29.750
that ransom money.
That knowledge,

01:29.834 --> 01:33.917
gentlemen and ladies,
was her means

01:34.000 --> 01:35.583
to commit this crime.

01:35.667 --> 01:40.458
Emily Dodson also had
a lustful desire

01:40.542 --> 01:43.667
to run off with her lover,
George Gannon.

01:43.750 --> 01:46.500
And that desire was her motive.

01:46.583 --> 01:48.333
As for opportunity?

01:49.291 --> 01:50.917
She was Charlie's mother!

01:51.000 --> 01:54.208
The person charged
with protecting him,

01:54.291 --> 01:58.709
an innocent, defenseless babe.

02:00.375 --> 02:04.625
Now, Emily Dodson had all
the opportunity in the world

02:04.709 --> 02:07.709
to put this plan into action.

02:09.000 --> 02:10.041
Means,

02:10.500 --> 02:11.750
motive,

02:11.834 --> 02:15.083
and opportunity,
and a child's life...

02:16.542 --> 02:17.583
cut short.

02:18.458 --> 02:20.375
(CLICKS TONGUE)

02:20.458 --> 02:24.250
Now, the defense over there
will try and confuse you

02:24.333 --> 02:26.917
with all sorts of wild theories

02:27.000 --> 02:30.208
and preposterous
propositions.

02:30.291 --> 02:34.792
Because his client is guilty,
and he knows it, all too well.

02:34.875 --> 02:39.792
But a trial is society's way

02:39.875 --> 02:42.000
of finding the truth,

02:42.083 --> 02:44.709
its way of seeking justice.

02:44.792 --> 02:48.166
Now, at the end of this trial,
I will ask each one of you,

02:48.250 --> 02:53.959
good people, to open your hearts
and find that truth,

02:54.542 --> 02:56.542
seek that justice.

02:56.625 --> 03:00.458
I will ask you to stare down
this woman

03:00.542 --> 03:05.917
who chose lust and money
over her child's life.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.458
Find Emily Dodson guilty...

03:10.375 --> 03:11.917
because she is guilty.

03:13.583 --> 03:17.083
I thank you kindly
for your time and attention.

03:18.291 --> 03:19.834
(JUDGE FRED WRIGHT
CLEARS THROAT)

03:19.917 --> 03:23.333
Mr. Mason,
we will hear you now.

03:32.834 --> 03:34.333
PERRY MASON: Good morning.

03:34.417 --> 03:35.792
(CLEARS THROAT)
My name is Perry Mason.

03:35.875 --> 03:39.166
I represent... Emily Dodson.

03:39.250 --> 03:43.208
Unlike Mr. Barnes here, who
spoke for a nearly two hours,

03:43.291 --> 03:46.000
I will be briefer-- uh, brief.

03:46.083 --> 03:49.166
Emily Dodson did not kill
her baby.

03:49.250 --> 03:51.834
Does anyone here really believe
she did? 'Cause I sure don't.

03:51.917 --> 03:55.041
Objection!
As to counsel's personal belief.

03:55.125 --> 03:56.625
Sustained.

03:56.709 --> 03:59.000
Sorry. Um, you may have heard,
I'm new to this.

03:59.083 --> 04:00.834
-Objection.
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Sustained.

04:00.917 --> 04:02.041
See what I mean?

04:03.417 --> 04:08.000
What really happened in December
of last year? (COUGHS)

04:09.291 --> 04:11.000
(VOICE BREAKS)
A good question.

04:11.083 --> 04:13.709
And although the defense...

04:13.792 --> 04:16.250
is under no obligation--
(COUGHS) I'm sorry.

04:16.333 --> 04:19.583
(COUGHS) Is under no obligation
to prove anything,

04:19.667 --> 04:21.542
it is natural to--
to want to know...

04:21.625 --> 04:23.291
(VOICE BREAKS)
...the whys, the whos,

04:23.375 --> 04:26.166
the whats and the wheres.
(COUGHS)

04:26.250 --> 04:27.583
Would you like a minute,
Mr. Mason?

04:27.667 --> 04:31.834
(COUGHS)
Uh, yeah, actually, just one--

04:35.166 --> 04:37.166
(COUGHING)

04:40.125 --> 04:41.417
(COUGHS)

04:42.583 --> 04:44.834
The prosecution--
(COUGHS)

04:52.709 --> 04:53.875
Thank you.

04:54.542 --> 04:56.417
The pro-- (GASPS)

04:56.500 --> 04:59.625
The prosecution's case
is completely

04:59.709 --> 05:03.166
and entirely circumstantial.

05:03.250 --> 05:06.875
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:06.959 --> 05:09.417
MASON: I rehearse it here,
I'm fine. I get up in court,

05:09.500 --> 05:12.000
my body won't do
what my head tells it to.

05:12.083 --> 05:14.083
You know,
same thing happens to me

05:14.166 --> 05:17.166
-when I gotta whiz in public.
I mostly use stalls.
-(TELEPHONE RINGS)

05:17.250 --> 05:18.792
HAZEL PRYSTOCK: Perry Mason,
Attorney-At-Law.

05:18.875 --> 05:22.083
Uh-huh. And is this in Oregon
or Utah, ma'am?

05:23.583 --> 05:25.625
Yes, I'm not sure
if this information qualifies

05:25.709 --> 05:28.333
as pertinent, ma'am.
The word means relevant.

05:28.417 --> 05:30.917
DELLA STREET:
Did George Gannon's place
have a garage?

05:31.000 --> 05:32.041
What? No.

05:32.125 --> 05:34.125
Well, in his opening,
Barnes says he has a garage.

05:34.208 --> 05:36.000
Well, DAs don't walk
crime scenes.

05:36.083 --> 05:38.417
I'm thinking you can hit
Barnes with a little buckshot.

05:38.500 --> 05:40.166
I mean, he got this wrong,
he got that wrong,

05:40.250 --> 05:42.291
the cops barely investigated
the case.

05:42.375 --> 05:45.083
And as you can see from this,
there's no garage.

05:45.166 --> 05:46.500
All right.
I'll take some pictures

05:46.583 --> 05:47.875
of a hedge
where a garage never was.

05:47.959 --> 05:49.875
No,
that's your investigator's job.

05:49.959 --> 05:51.875
You're Emily's lawyer now.
He'll do it.

05:51.959 --> 05:53.458
Yes, ma'am.
Anything else?

05:53.542 --> 05:56.041
Yeah. Something that connects
Sarecki and Nowak to Ennis.

05:56.125 --> 05:57.667
Actually,
anything would be nice.

05:57.750 --> 05:59.917
PETE STRICKLAND:
You think I ain't been looking
for Sarecki and Nowak?

06:00.000 --> 06:01.834
I run all their arrest records.
Nothing.

06:01.917 --> 06:03.792
Was Ennis ever up
in Milwaukee with these fucks?

06:03.875 --> 06:06.208
No. He's in Baltimore,
he's in Denver,

06:06.291 --> 06:07.458
then the war, then L.A.

06:07.542 --> 06:09.375
-What about George?
-PETE: Nothing there, either.

06:09.458 --> 06:11.709
It's like everybody
in this thing
is a complete fucking stranger.

06:11.792 --> 06:13.291
There's gotta be something
you missed.

06:13.375 --> 06:14.709
PETE: Well, feel free
to enlighten me.

06:14.792 --> 06:16.041
I've only been grinding
on this thing

06:16.125 --> 06:17.875
for a month and a half while
you've been screwing around

06:17.959 --> 06:19.917
-with your career change.
-Like I had a choice.

06:20.000 --> 06:21.250
-Oh, come on.
-"Come on," what?

06:21.333 --> 06:22.959
-PETE: You know what I mean.
-No, no, no. Enlighten me.

06:23.041 --> 06:24.667
-You know exactly
what I'm saying--
-MASON: No, no. I have no idea.

06:24.750 --> 06:26.208
-DELLA: Hey. Hey. Hey!
-What does that mean--

06:26.291 --> 06:27.458
This isn't helping.

06:30.166 --> 06:31.792
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:33.625 --> 06:35.583
Where are you going?

06:35.667 --> 06:39.583
Hm. To take pictures of a garage
that never was.

06:40.750 --> 06:42.333
Catch you later, Gloves.

06:42.417 --> 06:43.750
HAZEL: Toodle-oo, Pete.

06:45.291 --> 06:47.041
(DOOR CLOSES)

06:47.125 --> 06:48.875
First day,
and I already lost a juror

06:48.959 --> 06:50.250
'cause my throat locked up.

06:50.333 --> 06:51.834
DELLA:
No. It wasn't that.

06:52.875 --> 06:55.709
Seven was looking
at Emily the whole time.

06:55.792 --> 06:57.709
All nerves and tics.

06:59.333 --> 07:00.625
She looked guilty.

07:00.709 --> 07:03.375
(SCOFFS)
It's a hell of a start.

07:05.291 --> 07:06.667
(SIGHS)

07:06.750 --> 07:09.208
"Someday, George, my love,

07:10.417 --> 07:12.083
our dreams will come true,

07:12.166 --> 07:14.458
and we will be together forever.

07:14.542 --> 07:18.333
Until then,
I am and will always be...

07:20.417 --> 07:22.291
yours. (VOICE BREAKS) Emily."

07:24.000 --> 07:28.208
BARNES: Eleven love letters
from Emily to George Gannon

07:28.291 --> 07:29.959
in the span of four months.

07:30.041 --> 07:32.208
That last one
dated December 18th,

07:32.291 --> 07:35.417
less than two weeks
before the kidnapping.

07:35.500 --> 07:38.208
I'm sorry, Matthew.
I know this is difficult,

07:38.291 --> 07:41.000
but at the time
of the kidnapping,

07:41.083 --> 07:43.333
did the defendant tell you

07:43.417 --> 07:47.417
that she had anything to do
with George Gannon?

07:47.500 --> 07:49.917
-No.
-BARNES:
And when you were arrested,

07:50.000 --> 07:51.959
put in jail for kidnapping,

07:52.041 --> 07:54.500
did the defendant here tell you

07:54.583 --> 07:57.000
-she even knew George Gannon?
-No.

07:57.083 --> 07:59.250
BARNES: And when it became clear
that George Gannon

07:59.333 --> 08:01.125
was at the root
of these heinous crimes,

08:01.208 --> 08:02.959
did the defendant, your wife,

08:03.041 --> 08:05.959
tell you that she'd had
an intimate affair with him?

08:06.041 --> 08:09.750
No. She knew I was innocent,
and she let them put me in jail.

08:09.834 --> 08:11.625
-You were screwing that guy
for months--
-Oh!

08:11.709 --> 08:15.125
-MASON: Objection!
-Sustained.
Compose yourself, Mr. Dodson.

08:16.166 --> 08:17.750
BARNES: I have
no further questions.

08:20.083 --> 08:22.125
Mr. Mason, your witness.

08:24.250 --> 08:26.458
(CLEARS THROAT)
Um...

08:27.834 --> 08:30.667
Mr. Dodson, isn't--
isn't it true

08:30.750 --> 08:33.000
you're the secret love child
of Herman Baggerly?

08:33.083 --> 08:34.667
-BARNES: Objection.
-MASON: No, no, now, wait.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.000
I ca-- I can ask that.

08:36.083 --> 08:39.583
This has to do with this whole
motive... argument thing.

08:39.667 --> 08:42.000
Fair point,
albeit poorly phrased.

08:42.083 --> 08:43.083
Overruled.

08:43.166 --> 08:45.667
So, secret love child?
Yes or no.

08:45.750 --> 08:48.125
-Yes.
-And is Herman Baggerly

08:48.208 --> 08:50.208
a-- a wealthy guy?

08:50.291 --> 08:52.959
-I guess.
-MASON: You guess?

08:53.041 --> 08:55.500
He's up there with Vanderbilt
and Ford.

08:55.583 --> 08:59.041
Um, when did you first learn
that millionaire Herman Baggerly

08:59.125 --> 09:00.583
was your father?

09:00.667 --> 09:03.125
-About five years ago.
-MASON: So you packed Emily up

09:03.208 --> 09:05.083
and took her away
from her friends and family

09:05.166 --> 09:08.333
and moved her halfway
across the country. Did--

09:08.417 --> 09:11.291
did she know
that millionaire Herman Baggerly

09:11.375 --> 09:13.834
was your father before this?

09:13.917 --> 09:15.166
-No.
-MASON: Oh.

09:15.250 --> 09:16.291
It's a long drive from Missouri.

09:16.375 --> 09:18.000
-You tell her on the way?
-I can't tell you!

09:18.083 --> 09:19.166
MATTHEW DODSON:
No, I did not.

09:19.250 --> 09:21.583
Why can't you tell me?
I don't understand!

09:21.667 --> 09:23.959
MASON:
Well, that's life-changing news.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.834
Why did you keep it
from your wife?

09:25.917 --> 09:27.834
She didn't need to know
about it.

09:27.917 --> 09:29.375
Like you said, she's my wife.

09:29.458 --> 09:31.041
Oh, so you lied to her?

09:31.125 --> 09:33.667
I didn't tell her. That's all.

09:33.750 --> 09:35.917
Isn't it true on the night
Charlie was kidnapped,

09:36.000 --> 09:37.667
you were at a dice game?

09:38.208 --> 09:39.083
Yes.

09:39.166 --> 09:40.875
But at first,
you said you were at work.

09:40.959 --> 09:42.625
So you lied to the police?

09:42.709 --> 09:43.834
(CLEARS THROAT)

09:45.000 --> 09:46.333
I was embarrassed.

09:46.417 --> 09:48.250
MASON:
And because of your dice games,

09:48.333 --> 09:52.083
isn't it true, at one point,
you were some $3,000 in debt?

09:52.166 --> 09:54.959
-(GALLERY MUTTERING)
-Around there, yeah.

09:55.041 --> 09:57.417
Three thousand dollars.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.709
That's a lot of money
to most folks.

09:59.792 --> 10:01.709
How did--
how did you pay it off?

10:03.291 --> 10:04.625
(SOFTLY) My father.

10:06.000 --> 10:09.750
Uh, I-- I-- I think
he said his-- his father.

10:09.834 --> 10:11.083
That's Herman Baggerly there.

10:11.166 --> 10:13.417
He covered your gambling debts,
is that correct?

10:13.500 --> 10:14.917
I just said he did, didn't I?

10:15.041 --> 10:17.458
Is it also true
that you were arrested

10:17.542 --> 10:19.458
for Charlie's kidnapping
and murder?

10:19.542 --> 10:21.000
-Yes.
-MASON: And because of that,

10:21.083 --> 10:23.834
you spent, let me see,
a whole day and a half in jail

10:23.917 --> 10:26.291
until the lawyer that
your very wealthy father hired

10:26.375 --> 10:27.625
got you out, is that correct?

10:27.709 --> 10:30.083
-Yes, that's correct.
-So, in your opinion,

10:30.166 --> 10:32.375
were the police incompetent
to arrest you?

10:32.458 --> 10:34.667
-They made a mistake.
-MASON: Or were they right
to suspect you?

10:34.750 --> 10:37.041
Because despite all your lying,
you're sitting here

10:37.125 --> 10:38.959
with your gambling debts
wiped clean,

10:39.041 --> 10:41.959
your business bailed out,
and you now live in a mansion.

10:42.041 --> 10:44.500
It sure looks like you've
benefited from Charlie's death.

10:44.583 --> 10:46.083
-Objection!
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Sustained.

10:46.166 --> 10:48.625
Strike from the record.
The jury will disregard that.

10:48.709 --> 10:50.959
She's the one who's guilty,
not me!

10:51.041 --> 10:52.750
I asked about the kidnapping
of your son,

10:52.834 --> 10:54.834
-not whether she's guil--
-Who says he's my son?

10:56.041 --> 10:57.333
I'm sorry. What?

10:57.417 --> 10:59.375
Who says he's my son?

10:59.458 --> 11:02.333
How can you believe
a word she says?

11:02.417 --> 11:04.834
She ruined my life!
I hope they hang you,

11:04.917 --> 11:06.166
you lying whore!

11:06.250 --> 11:10.375
-(GALLERY MURMURS, EXCLAIMS)
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Order! Order!

11:10.458 --> 11:12.667
Mr. Dodson,
you will control yourself,

11:12.750 --> 11:15.750
or I will hold you in contempt.

11:15.834 --> 11:18.083
No further questions,
Your Honor.

11:20.083 --> 11:22.458
(LAUGHTER)

11:24.625 --> 11:25.875
(BICYCLE BELL RINGING)

11:26.583 --> 11:30.458
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:34.041 --> 11:35.583
(HAMMERING)

11:39.709 --> 11:41.166
-(CAMERA CLICKS)
-Voilà.

11:45.667 --> 11:48.291
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

11:51.458 --> 11:53.959
(WORKERS WHISPERING IN SPANISH)

11:59.250 --> 12:03.000
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:39.792 --> 12:41.417
JUDGE WRIGHT: Call
your next witness, Mr. Barnes.

12:41.500 --> 12:44.250
-How's she doing with the jury?
-Pretty good, considering.

12:44.333 --> 12:47.583
I think Two and Eleven
almost feel sorry for her.

12:47.667 --> 12:50.834
BARNES: (CLEARS THROAT)
The people call Terrence Smith.

12:51.333 --> 12:52.542
(DOOR OPENS)

13:01.166 --> 13:03.917
Hold on. Judge, we're--
we're, uh-- We're not prepared

13:04.000 --> 13:06.083
for this gentleman
to be called today.

13:06.166 --> 13:08.291
BARNES:
Uh, I'm sorry, Your Honor,

13:08.375 --> 13:13.083
Mr. Smith, uh, is
unavailable later. Travel plans.

13:13.166 --> 13:15.542
Beg the court's indulgence
on this.

13:17.041 --> 13:18.792
-We don't have a file on him.
-I'm-- I'm sorry,

13:18.875 --> 13:20.750
we don't have any discovery
material on this guy.

13:20.834 --> 13:22.583
BARNES: Judge, I-- I assure you
we turned over

13:22.667 --> 13:25.458
the discovery material to
the defendant's former counsel,

13:25.542 --> 13:27.125
-Frank C. Dillon.
-Well, I assure you

13:27.208 --> 13:29.750
-we don't have it.
-Well, you can have my copy.

13:29.834 --> 13:32.959
It's just a one-page
detective's report, Your Honor.

13:33.041 --> 13:34.291
The length isn't the issue.

13:34.375 --> 13:35.709
My client is fighting
for her life

13:35.792 --> 13:37.250
and the DA's withholding
discovery,

13:37.333 --> 13:39.750
and, I'm sorry, "travel plans"?

13:39.834 --> 13:42.542
Is there some kind of court
smell test we could do here?

13:42.625 --> 13:44.750
Mr. Barnes, you better
make sure the defense

13:44.834 --> 13:47.125
has every document
in this case going forward.

13:47.208 --> 13:49.333
I will not be granting
adjournments

13:49.417 --> 13:51.750
for discovery disputes.

13:51.834 --> 13:54.834
Very well, Your Honor.
I'll-- I'll make certain.

13:54.917 --> 13:56.333
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Swear the witness.

13:56.417 --> 13:58.375
BAILIFF:
Do you swear the testimony
you're about to give

13:58.458 --> 13:59.667
shall be the truth,
the whole truth,

13:59.750 --> 14:01.750
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

14:02.417 --> 14:03.458
TERRENCE SMITH:
I swear.

14:03.542 --> 14:05.458
-You know this guy?
-I don't think so.

14:05.542 --> 14:07.166
Well, he seems to know you.

14:07.250 --> 14:10.500
BARNES: Kindly state your name
and occupation for the record.

14:10.583 --> 14:11.750
My name is Terrence Smith.

14:11.834 --> 14:14.333
I am the manager
of the Star Hotel.

14:14.417 --> 14:17.875
Hmm, and do you know
the defendant, Emily Dodson?

14:18.583 --> 14:20.166
SMITH: I've seen her.

14:20.250 --> 14:21.542
Just the one time.

14:21.625 --> 14:25.333
Would you describe
that occasion to the jury?

14:25.417 --> 14:28.458
This past November the 12th,
a man came into the hotel,

14:28.542 --> 14:30.959
asking for adjoining rooms.

14:31.041 --> 14:33.959
That's where I saw her,
the defendant,

14:34.041 --> 14:36.125
sitting outside in the car
waiting for him

14:36.208 --> 14:38.083
to sign the registry here.

14:38.166 --> 14:40.000
Oh, what name did he sign?

14:40.959 --> 14:43.917
Mr. and Mrs. Stanley Kelly.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.959
SMITH: He paid me in advance,
and I gave him the keys

14:47.041 --> 14:48.500
and he went back to his car.

14:49.583 --> 14:51.333
Did you see this couple again?

14:52.458 --> 14:53.625
Nope.

14:55.041 --> 14:57.709
I mean, no, sir.

14:57.792 --> 15:01.458
Did anything unusual happen
shortly after they checked in?

15:01.542 --> 15:03.125
(CLEARS THROAT) Yes, sir.

15:03.667 --> 15:05.458
(EMILY DODSON MOANING)

15:05.542 --> 15:09.250
As I was doing my rounds about
an hour after they checked in,

15:09.333 --> 15:12.458
I pass by their rooms,
and I hear this baby crying.

15:12.542 --> 15:13.792
(EMILY MOANING)

15:13.875 --> 15:15.625
(CHARLIE COOING)

15:15.709 --> 15:19.417
SMITH: I was concerned,
so I knocked on the door.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.375
-(CHARLIE BABBLING)
-No one answered.

15:21.458 --> 15:23.792
-(CHARLIE WAILS)
-SMITH: Then I continued

15:23.875 --> 15:26.250
to follow the cries
around the corner

15:26.333 --> 15:27.667
to the adjoining room.

15:28.792 --> 15:32.417
I used my room key,
I went in,

15:32.500 --> 15:34.917
-and I find this baby...
-(CHARLIE CRYING)

15:35.000 --> 15:38.959
...alone on the bed,
bawling his little eyes out.

15:39.667 --> 15:41.750
Hmm. What did you do?

15:41.834 --> 15:43.166
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

15:43.250 --> 15:45.792
SMITH: Well, through
the connecting door,

15:45.875 --> 15:49.542
I heard sounds of, uh...

15:50.709 --> 15:51.792
lovemaking.

15:51.875 --> 15:53.500
(GALLERY MURMURING)

15:53.583 --> 15:55.417
SMITH:
I was disgusted.

15:55.500 --> 16:00.417
I mean, who leaves a baby
all alone to have sex?

16:00.500 --> 16:03.041
BARNES: Fair question.
What did you do?

16:03.125 --> 16:06.333
SMITH: I banged on the door.
I yelled at them to stop,

16:06.417 --> 16:07.792
to take care of the baby,

16:07.875 --> 16:09.417
or else I was going
to call the police.

16:09.500 --> 16:13.333
Hmm. And did you later find out
the real name of the man

16:13.417 --> 16:17.166
-who checked in to those rooms?
-George Gannon.

16:17.250 --> 16:19.917
-(GALLERY EXCLAIMS)
-BARNES: And the woman?

16:20.000 --> 16:21.709
SMITH: She's right there.

16:22.709 --> 16:23.875
Emily Dodson.

16:23.959 --> 16:26.542
-(GALLERY EXCLAIMS)
-BARNES: Any doubt in your mind?

16:27.625 --> 16:30.417
No, sir. That's the woman.

16:32.208 --> 16:34.625
Thank you. No further questions.

16:34.709 --> 16:36.250
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Mr. Mason?

16:37.125 --> 16:38.625
You may proceed.

16:40.291 --> 16:43.625
Love letters and stolen kisses,
that's what you told me!

16:43.709 --> 16:46.375
It was George's idea,
and the door wasn't closed!

16:46.458 --> 16:47.667
I left the door open!

16:47.750 --> 16:49.875
Oh, I'll be sure to get that
on record.

16:49.959 --> 16:52.500
"It's okay, folks,
she could see Charlie

16:52.583 --> 16:55.208
the whole time George was
pounding away on top of her!"

16:55.291 --> 16:57.834
Do you have any idea
what everyone in that courtroom

16:57.917 --> 16:58.917
now thinks?

16:59.000 --> 17:01.208
That if you're okay
to leave your kid alone

17:01.291 --> 17:05.041
while you have a "stolen kiss"
with George as he fucks you,

17:05.125 --> 17:07.667
then maybe you're okay
to let George kidnap Charlie

17:07.750 --> 17:08.667
for a day or two.

17:08.750 --> 17:10.417
That is why
you tell me everything,

17:10.500 --> 17:14.083
-so I can be fucking prepared.
-Then where is Charlie's killer?

17:14.166 --> 17:15.792
You promised you'd find him!

17:18.542 --> 17:19.625
(SCOFFS)

17:22.041 --> 17:24.917
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:31.792 --> 17:33.417
I want to show you something.

17:42.041 --> 17:43.375
Faith.

17:43.458 --> 17:45.375
Every single one
of these gifts is...

17:45.458 --> 17:49.375
someone's prayer for redemption,

17:49.458 --> 17:52.542
for relief from suffering.

17:52.625 --> 17:55.083
For something bigger
than themselves.

17:55.166 --> 17:57.667
Isn't that something
you ever feel?

17:57.750 --> 18:00.000
If I say yes,
can I go back to work?

18:00.083 --> 18:02.709
SISTER ALICE MCKEEGAN: You were
really hard on Emily just now.

18:02.792 --> 18:04.500
Yeah. For good reason.

18:04.583 --> 18:08.083
She didn't tell you
because she was ashamed.

18:08.166 --> 18:11.000
Haven't you ever done something
that you're ashamed of?

18:11.083 --> 18:12.500
Of course I have.

18:14.125 --> 18:15.166
Have you?

18:15.667 --> 18:16.667
Yes.

18:18.667 --> 18:20.959
How is your Easter Sunday
looking?

18:24.917 --> 18:26.291
I don't honestly know.

18:28.458 --> 18:31.041
I gotta say, Sister,
you're not what I expected.

18:31.125 --> 18:34.166
You were thinking Joan of Arc?

18:34.250 --> 18:37.208
The Maid from Heaven with
a quivering throb in her voice?

18:37.291 --> 18:40.333
"I'd rather die than do
something I know to be a sin."

18:40.417 --> 18:42.000
Something like that. Yeah.

18:42.709 --> 18:43.959
Why would that be any more real

18:44.041 --> 18:45.709
than what's standing
in front of you?

18:46.417 --> 18:48.041
I honestly don't know.

18:49.875 --> 18:52.959
You were good with Matthew
on the stand today.

18:53.041 --> 18:54.917
You're better
than you think you are.

18:55.750 --> 18:57.166
Faith, huh?

18:57.250 --> 18:58.834
SISTER ALICE:
Something like that.

19:00.166 --> 19:02.625
MASON: Don't come
to court tomorrow.

19:02.709 --> 19:05.208
I know you think you're helping,
but you're not.

19:11.709 --> 19:13.041
(DOOR CLOSES)

19:21.291 --> 19:22.834
And this is?

19:22.917 --> 19:24.959
When you accused
the DA of withholding,

19:25.041 --> 19:27.333
it seems he took every piece
of evidence they had

19:27.417 --> 19:29.333
and maybe nine
or ten unrelated cases,

19:29.417 --> 19:32.125
tossed them up in the air, and
threw them back in the boxes.

19:32.208 --> 19:33.417
The ol' dumperoo.

19:34.750 --> 19:36.333
This is from 1909.

19:36.417 --> 19:38.333
Cat got stuck in a drainpipe.

19:38.417 --> 19:39.667
DELLA: It's not all bad.

19:39.750 --> 19:41.667
Hazel actually got
a pertinent tip

19:41.750 --> 19:43.458
from Sarecki's last landlord.

19:43.542 --> 19:46.417
A man calling in from Milwaukee
said he rented Sarecki

19:46.500 --> 19:47.667
a room in his house.

19:47.750 --> 19:50.500
Said Sarecki gave him references
from his old landlord.

19:50.583 --> 19:51.875
And guess where that was?

19:51.959 --> 19:53.166
-Denver.
-Denver.

19:53.250 --> 19:56.125
Remember Denver? Ennis worked
as a Pinkerton there.

19:56.208 --> 19:59.125
Sarecki was in the same town
at the same time as Ennis.

20:00.458 --> 20:01.667
What about Nowak?

20:01.750 --> 20:04.917
Well, the tipster didn't rent
a room to Nowak.

20:05.000 --> 20:06.542
PETE:
We even got an address.

20:06.625 --> 20:08.291
Could be the connection
you're looking for.

20:08.375 --> 20:10.083
To prove what?
That Sarecki and Ennis

20:10.166 --> 20:11.959
were in Denver
at the same time

20:12.041 --> 20:14.583
in 19-fucking-whatever?
What does that prove?

20:15.792 --> 20:17.208
We got killed in there today.

20:17.291 --> 20:20.792
I have no fucking idea
what I'm gonna do tomorrow.

20:21.834 --> 20:23.083
And now this shit.

20:27.458 --> 20:29.750
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

20:30.291 --> 20:33.500
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

20:35.625 --> 20:39.417
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

20:49.500 --> 20:50.959
(MASON SNIFFS)

20:52.667 --> 20:55.041
(WORKERS LAUGHING)

20:57.083 --> 20:59.166
Found something
at Gannon's house.

21:01.834 --> 21:03.333
"What is it, Pete?"

21:04.375 --> 21:05.750
Well, Perry, it's this.

21:05.834 --> 21:08.250
Two uncashed checks
from Radiant Assembly of God,

21:08.333 --> 21:11.041
made out to something
called Sunroot Services, Inc.

21:11.125 --> 21:12.750
Seems Sunroot Services

21:12.834 --> 21:15.208
has the same address
as George Gannon.

21:16.166 --> 21:17.542
And if you look at the checks,

21:17.625 --> 21:21.875
you'll see the stamped signature
of one Eric Q. Seidel.

21:22.000 --> 21:23.250
Not sure what the "Q" is for,

21:23.333 --> 21:24.875
but the address
and the hinky signature

21:24.959 --> 21:28.208
might mean that our boy George
was stealing from the church.

21:29.208 --> 21:31.083
"Say, Pete,
that's pretty interesting.

21:31.166 --> 21:32.875
What's it got to do
with Emily?"

21:32.959 --> 21:34.041
I don't know.

21:34.125 --> 21:36.458
"What were Ennis and Sarecki
up to in Denver?"

21:36.542 --> 21:38.000
I couldn't say.

21:38.083 --> 21:40.000
"What should I do
in court tomorrow?"

21:44.542 --> 21:46.583
-You should use the teeth.
-(MASON SIGHS)

21:46.667 --> 21:48.959
What's this colored cop to you?

21:49.041 --> 21:51.834
You think he's some kind
of boy scout?

21:51.917 --> 21:54.458
He's just as bad as the rest
of those bulls, Perry.

21:54.542 --> 21:56.834
Looking the other way,
keeping his mouth shut,

21:56.917 --> 21:58.583
trying to save his own ass.

21:58.667 --> 22:00.458
I got no respect for it.

22:00.542 --> 22:02.083
I gave him my word, Pete.

22:02.166 --> 22:03.875
Oh, yeah?
What'd you give to Emily?

22:04.000 --> 22:06.041
'Cause Barnes is dancing her
to the gallows

22:06.125 --> 22:07.667
while you sit on your hands.

22:07.750 --> 22:10.250
Use these and get me to Denver.

22:10.333 --> 22:12.083
It's the only chance she's got.

22:14.583 --> 22:18.083
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:28.208 --> 22:30.667
I use this,
Drake is fucked.

22:30.750 --> 22:32.542
He's a cop.

22:32.625 --> 22:35.125
-Will they kill him?
-They could.

22:35.208 --> 22:37.250
Well, "could" is different
from "will."

22:37.333 --> 22:39.166
There's also being true
to my word.

22:39.250 --> 22:41.458
LUPE GIBBS: Looks to me
like if you don't use it,

22:41.542 --> 22:43.458
that lady gets the rope.

22:43.542 --> 22:46.291
All they've got is innuendo
and circumstance.

22:48.041 --> 22:50.250
I think I liked you better
when you was a bum.

22:50.959 --> 22:52.583
Least I could understand you.

22:53.000 --> 22:54.125
(SIGHS)

22:54.959 --> 22:56.333
Give me the bottle.

22:57.458 --> 22:58.917
-No.
-MASON: Come on.

22:59.000 --> 23:00.041
I'm not gonna sleep tonight.

23:00.125 --> 23:01.458
-Give me the bottle.
-No.

23:02.834 --> 23:05.667
♪ (SOFT JAZZ MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO) ♪

23:10.291 --> 23:11.792
If I make a mistake...

23:12.542 --> 23:13.792
someone dies.

23:16.583 --> 23:18.250
Then don't make a mistake.

23:21.750 --> 23:23.792
(SIGHS)

23:23.875 --> 23:25.625
How long to fly to Denver?

23:27.458 --> 23:30.917
BARNES: Now, your report
mentions a trail of blood.

23:31.000 --> 23:32.250
Did you follow it?

23:32.333 --> 23:35.083
-PAUL DRAKE: Yes, sir.
-BARNES: And where did it lead?

23:35.166 --> 23:37.709
DRAKE: Down the fire escape
to the street.

23:37.792 --> 23:42.125
BARNES: To where George Gannon
presumably parked his car

23:42.208 --> 23:43.500
for his escape?

23:44.333 --> 23:46.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

23:46.917 --> 23:48.667
That's, uh,
what the detectives say.

23:48.750 --> 23:50.875
-Yes, sir.
-Thank you, officer.

23:50.959 --> 23:53.083
No further questions.

23:53.166 --> 23:55.166
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Mr. Mason, your witness.

23:58.166 --> 23:59.291
Mr. Mason.

24:03.542 --> 24:04.542
Um...

24:08.000 --> 24:09.875
Officer Drake, um...

24:13.834 --> 24:15.542
Can I please get
the photographs?

24:18.208 --> 24:20.291
Can you tell us...

24:20.375 --> 24:22.583
what it is we're seeing here?

24:24.250 --> 24:26.000
DRAKE: As I said before,
this is a photograph

24:26.083 --> 24:28.041
of the dead bodies
left at the crime scene.

24:29.709 --> 24:30.875
And this one?

24:31.709 --> 24:33.542
DRAKE:
The gun left at the scene.

24:34.875 --> 24:36.458
How about this one?

24:36.542 --> 24:39.250
DRAKE: Shell casings
that I described earlier.

24:39.333 --> 24:43.083
MASON: Now, you just mentioned
a trail of blood

24:43.166 --> 24:45.291
that led down the hallway
and onto the fire escape,

24:45.375 --> 24:47.208
-is that correct?
-Yes, I did.

24:47.291 --> 24:50.000
How long would you say
that trail was?

24:50.083 --> 24:54.750
Maybe 20 feet down the hallway,
another 20 or so to the street?

24:54.834 --> 24:57.709
A 40-foot trail of blood.

24:59.083 --> 25:03.041
Wow. That-- uh, that's about...
(EXHALES)

25:07.375 --> 25:09.834
(GALLERY MURMURING)

25:09.917 --> 25:12.917
Wow. That's-- that's
about from me to you.

25:14.208 --> 25:16.250
That's a pretty long trail...

25:18.583 --> 25:19.959
wouldn't you say?

25:20.792 --> 25:22.250
Yes.

25:22.333 --> 25:24.458
MASON: Would you please show
the members of the jury

25:24.542 --> 25:29.333
the photographs that depict
this 40-foot trail of blood?

25:29.417 --> 25:30.458
(CLEARS THROAT)

25:34.875 --> 25:36.792
Well, I don't see any here.

25:38.333 --> 25:39.333
Oh.

25:40.291 --> 25:41.542
Thank you.

25:41.625 --> 25:43.375
(DRAKE SIGHS)

25:43.458 --> 25:45.500
Officer Drake, um,

25:45.583 --> 25:48.875
who was the first responding
homicide detective? Thank you.

25:48.959 --> 25:51.542
That would be Detective Ennis.

25:51.625 --> 25:54.208
And did he arrive with
his partner, Detective Holcomb?

25:54.291 --> 25:55.709
DRAKE: No,
Detective Ennis arrived alone.

25:55.792 --> 25:58.000
But other detectives
and Detective Holcomb

25:58.083 --> 25:59.417
were there pretty soon after.

26:01.291 --> 26:03.875
Does it seem odd to you
that Detective Ennis

26:03.959 --> 26:06.667
was also first at Angel's Flight

26:06.750 --> 26:09.500
and among the first at
George Gannon's alleged suicide?

26:09.583 --> 26:13.166
Objection! Compound question,
calls for speculation.

26:13.250 --> 26:15.458
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Agree on both counts. Sustained.

26:15.542 --> 26:17.792
Really don't want him
to answer that, do you?

26:17.875 --> 26:18.917
Your Honor...

26:19.000 --> 26:20.917
Address your questions
to the witness, Mr. Mason.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.917
MASON: Certainly, Judge.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.917
Officer Drake,
during your investigation,

26:26.000 --> 26:28.792
did you recover
any physical evidence

26:28.875 --> 26:32.333
that pertains to this case?

26:35.333 --> 26:37.542
I'm sorry,
can you repeat the question?

26:37.625 --> 26:39.917
Did you recover
any physical evidence

26:40.000 --> 26:41.375
from the crime scene?

26:44.083 --> 26:45.417
No, I did not.

26:45.500 --> 26:47.834
Not one piece
of physical evidence?

26:47.917 --> 26:49.250
Objection.
Asked and answered.

26:49.333 --> 26:51.083
If you're getting
at something, Mr. Mason,

26:51.166 --> 26:53.667
-please get there.
-Your Honor, I have, um...

26:59.083 --> 27:00.542
I have no further questions.

27:01.417 --> 27:03.750
(CLEARS THROAT)
Just fishing.

27:03.834 --> 27:06.208
JUDGE WRIGHT:
The witness is excused.

27:06.291 --> 27:08.709
The jury is adjourned
for the day.

27:08.792 --> 27:10.792
You are reminded not to discuss
the case

27:10.875 --> 27:12.750
with each other
or with anyone else,

27:12.834 --> 27:16.625
and to refrain from looking
at any newspaper coverage.

27:16.709 --> 27:21.333
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:21.417 --> 27:23.583
(INAUDIBLE)

27:29.291 --> 27:31.625
ELDER BROWN: Ten days
till Easter Sunday,

27:31.709 --> 27:34.125
ladies and gentlemen.
Ten days to the resurrection,

27:34.208 --> 27:37.792
the apparent resurrection
of Charlie the baby.

27:37.875 --> 27:39.834
Down with McKeeganism!

27:39.917 --> 27:41.583
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

27:45.250 --> 27:47.667
-(DOOR OPENS)
-ELDER SEIDEL: Mr. Mason?

27:47.750 --> 27:50.792
What are you doing in here?
This room is not open to you.

27:50.875 --> 27:53.917
-He said he had permission.
-ELDER SEIDEL: He does not.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.667
-Put away the camera.
-Relax, Deacon.

27:56.750 --> 27:58.959
We're about to make your church
look good.

27:59.041 --> 28:02.000
We think George Gannon
was stealing from you.

28:02.083 --> 28:04.041
Do you have any idea
why your former accountant

28:04.125 --> 28:06.500
was sending checks to a company
with his home address

28:06.583 --> 28:08.125
as the corporate headquarters?

28:09.375 --> 28:11.041
Clearly, we weren't aware of

28:11.125 --> 28:14.083
most of what George Gannon
was doing in this room.

28:14.166 --> 28:16.750
He's brought nothing
but the worst attention upon us.

28:18.041 --> 28:20.208
I'm sorry,
what's Sunroot Services?

28:20.291 --> 28:22.875
I-- I believe
it's an agricultural business

28:22.959 --> 28:25.041
that our church
has some investments in.

28:25.125 --> 28:27.959
We probably have over
30 subsidiary businesses

28:28.041 --> 28:30.542
-in our endowment.
-Looks more like 50 or 60.

28:30.625 --> 28:32.583
ELDER SEIDEL:
If our church relied solely

28:32.667 --> 28:34.709
on the donations
of the assembly,

28:34.792 --> 28:36.875
we'd be a much smaller ministry.

28:36.959 --> 28:38.250
(MASON CHUCKLES)

28:38.333 --> 28:40.250
And here was me thinking
you were just hucksters

28:40.333 --> 28:43.500
shaking down the hicks
and the rubes, Mr. Seidel.

28:43.583 --> 28:47.291
Um, Mr. Seidel, who's J.H.?

28:47.375 --> 28:48.458
ELDER SEIDEL: J.H.?

28:48.542 --> 28:50.417
-MASON: Yeah.
-ELDER SEIDEL: Mm-hm.

28:50.500 --> 28:53.375
MASON: I'm not very good
with numbers and such.

28:53.458 --> 28:55.667
Down here there's "G.G."
George Gannon's hand.

28:55.750 --> 28:58.125
But up here, where the new
companies were starting up,

28:58.208 --> 29:00.291
there's a "J.H."

29:00.375 --> 29:02.875
Big "J," skinny "H."

29:02.959 --> 29:05.417
Mr. Mason, what does this have
to do with the defense

29:05.500 --> 29:06.667
of Emily Dodson,

29:06.750 --> 29:09.041
wh-- which we are charitably
paying you for?

29:09.125 --> 29:11.291
Uh, well, if George Gannon

29:11.375 --> 29:13.333
was stealing from you,
and trying to cover it up

29:13.417 --> 29:14.959
with the Dodson ransom,
that's motive.

29:15.041 --> 29:16.917
DELLA: Or he's just
a professional thief.

29:17.000 --> 29:19.625
Either way, it's good for Emily.

29:19.709 --> 29:23.625
And, um, you might wanna
stop payment on those checks.

29:24.583 --> 29:25.625
Thank you.

29:26.166 --> 29:27.208
(DOOR CLOSES)

29:28.250 --> 29:29.959
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

29:34.375 --> 29:36.000
Miss Nina said
you wanted to see me, sir?

29:36.083 --> 29:38.500
JOE MORTON: I heard
you spoke well in court today.

29:38.583 --> 29:41.667
Made this whole shitcan precinct
look good.

29:45.166 --> 29:48.750
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

29:50.834 --> 29:52.709
This is the time
you say thank you.

29:54.291 --> 29:56.667
-Thank you, sir.
-Great. Now beat it.

30:02.709 --> 30:04.792
You were the first detective
on the scene

30:04.875 --> 30:07.166
when Charlie Dodson's body
was discovered, correct?

30:07.250 --> 30:09.709
-DETECTIVE ENNIS:
Yes, that's correct.
-And how did you come to be

30:09.792 --> 30:11.375
the first detective
on the scene?

30:11.458 --> 30:13.041
I was having dinner
with the Elks

30:13.125 --> 30:15.250
when the commotion
kicked up outside.

30:15.333 --> 30:17.625
BARNES: Mm-hmm.
And was Detective Ray Royce

30:17.709 --> 30:21.041
first up on homicide calls
on the night in question?

30:22.875 --> 30:24.125
-What?
-BARNES: Did you pay

30:24.208 --> 30:26.500
Watch Commander McGuire
to jump Royce

30:26.583 --> 30:28.750
and get assigned lead
on the case, Detective Ennis?

30:28.834 --> 30:30.709
-What the fuck is this bullshit?
-Maybe that's something

30:30.792 --> 30:32.125
you should've shared
with your partner.

30:32.208 --> 30:35.000
Did you pay off
the Watch Commander?

30:35.083 --> 30:37.709
You're telling me McGuire's
gonna get on the stand,

30:37.792 --> 30:39.417
say he took money
to move me up?

30:39.500 --> 30:41.583
What happened
to that blood trail, detective?

30:41.667 --> 30:42.834
Who gives a fuck?

30:42.917 --> 30:44.333
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB: If you
can't answer those questions,

30:44.417 --> 30:46.500
Mason's gonna rip you
a new asshole up there.

30:46.583 --> 30:48.375
Fuck Mason.
I can handle him.

30:48.458 --> 30:49.875
BARNES:
Let's try this again.

30:49.959 --> 30:51.875
You were the first detective
on the scene

30:51.959 --> 30:54.875
when Charlie Dodson's body
was discovered, correct?

30:56.250 --> 30:58.625
-Yes, that's correct.
-Thank you.

31:05.333 --> 31:07.375
Emily's signature,
as promised.

31:07.458 --> 31:09.625
Matthew Dodson will need to
sign the release as well.

31:09.709 --> 31:11.375
He disowned the child in court.

31:11.458 --> 31:12.542
Under an oath to God.

31:12.625 --> 31:14.041
I've been assured
that this will suffice.

31:14.125 --> 31:16.375
You know, she signed this
just to make you happy.

31:16.458 --> 31:17.750
You see that, right?

31:17.834 --> 31:19.750
She doesn't actually
want her baby dug up.

31:19.834 --> 31:21.166
Emily has faith.

31:21.250 --> 31:24.125
You're the one who doesn't
want this to happen, Mother.

31:24.208 --> 31:26.959
Nevertheless, arrangements for
your service are still ongoing.

31:27.041 --> 31:29.166
I would like to be
at the cemetery

31:29.250 --> 31:30.500
before Easter Services.

31:30.583 --> 31:32.291
I'm going to need all
my strength

31:32.375 --> 31:33.917
to become His instrument.

31:35.291 --> 31:37.875
I've also made
other arrangements.

31:37.959 --> 31:39.375
Come.

31:39.458 --> 31:43.166
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

31:47.625 --> 31:51.000
These are the other arrangements
that are ongoing.

31:51.083 --> 31:52.917
No.
We're not running from this.

31:53.000 --> 31:54.750
Stop. Hey. Do you understand?

31:54.834 --> 31:57.250
It's not just Elder Brown
and his billboard.

31:57.333 --> 31:59.458
We are surrounded by those
who cannot wait

31:59.542 --> 32:01.750
for Easter Sunday.
They can't wait for our ruin.

32:01.834 --> 32:04.208
-If ruin is God's--
-(GRUNTS)

32:04.291 --> 32:06.583
We have to run, okay?

32:06.667 --> 32:08.333
This church is mine!

32:08.834 --> 32:10.166
Mine!

32:10.250 --> 32:12.083
The Assembly, the Temple,

32:12.166 --> 32:13.875
every cornerstone
of every church

32:13.959 --> 32:15.083
we've ever built.

32:15.166 --> 32:16.834
Do you remember saying that?

32:18.166 --> 32:20.667
I'm remembering a lot of things,
lately, Mama.

32:21.709 --> 32:23.291
You want to run?

32:23.375 --> 32:25.250
Go ahead and run.

32:25.333 --> 32:28.458
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

32:28.542 --> 32:30.166
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-DELLA: City records?

32:30.250 --> 32:32.083
MASON: Yes, I know
you'd rather be in court, Della.

32:32.166 --> 32:33.250
I'd rather be tracking
the leads.

32:33.333 --> 32:35.125
But someone's
gotta dog this ledger,

32:35.208 --> 32:36.667
and Strick's already on his way
to Denver.

32:36.750 --> 32:38.834
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
-At least he should be.

32:39.583 --> 32:40.750
I gotta go.

32:41.333 --> 32:42.375
Who is it?

32:43.542 --> 32:46.166
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

32:48.875 --> 32:50.041
Who is it?

32:57.542 --> 32:58.834
Officer Drake?

33:00.041 --> 33:02.208
Perry Mason, Esquire,
may I come in?

33:03.375 --> 33:04.375
Of course.

33:13.500 --> 33:14.500
This a social call?

33:14.583 --> 33:16.250
DRAKE: Something
I have to say to you.

33:17.500 --> 33:20.208
I wanted to tell them, Mason.

33:20.291 --> 33:22.583
I wanted to tell them everything
when you asked me.

33:22.667 --> 33:25.000
Well,
I shouldn't have asked you.

33:25.083 --> 33:27.750
-I gave you my word.
-DRAKE: But you kept your word.

33:29.041 --> 33:30.959
Yes, I did.

33:31.041 --> 33:32.875
DRAKE:
I almost wanted you to...

33:32.959 --> 33:35.041
force my hand,
so that I could...

33:38.208 --> 33:40.000
so that I could blame you.

33:40.083 --> 33:42.166
MASON:
Oh, you're just saying that now.

33:42.250 --> 33:44.041
DRAKE: I could've helped
that woman.

33:44.834 --> 33:46.750
I could've, but...

33:49.083 --> 33:50.166
I was afraid.

33:50.250 --> 33:52.250
MASON: Look, the deck
was stacked from the start.

33:52.333 --> 33:53.750
Anyone would've made
the same choice.

33:53.834 --> 33:55.542
'Cause there wasn't one.

33:55.625 --> 33:57.458
You know what it's like
to be afraid?

33:59.417 --> 34:00.750
I was in the war.

34:02.375 --> 34:05.291
Every day, I gotta wake up with
this ball of fear inside of me.

34:06.583 --> 34:08.458
Gotta go put on that uniform,

34:09.917 --> 34:12.667
go out there and play the fool.

34:12.750 --> 34:15.458
You know there's not one
black officer assigned

34:15.542 --> 34:16.959
to work with a white officer?

34:17.917 --> 34:19.375
Not one.

34:19.458 --> 34:22.709
We all on foot patrol,
by ourselves,

34:22.792 --> 34:24.625
keeping the coloreds in check.

34:26.083 --> 34:28.291
Hell, they won't even let me
cuff white folks.

34:29.041 --> 34:30.834
'Cause a black man, even...

34:31.625 --> 34:33.041
a goddamn black police officer,

34:33.125 --> 34:35.000
can never stand up
to a white man.

34:35.542 --> 34:36.542
Never.

34:37.750 --> 34:39.208
Even a goddamn white criminal.

34:39.291 --> 34:42.500
A white fucking murderer
gets to look down on me.

34:45.667 --> 34:47.709
You have any idea
what that feels like?

34:48.375 --> 34:49.375
No.

34:50.667 --> 34:52.959
Every day, I'm scared, Mason,

34:53.041 --> 34:55.125
that I'm going
to let it all out.

35:02.750 --> 35:04.291
(DRAKE SIGHS)

35:14.333 --> 35:16.542
What they give me
for being a good boy.

35:16.625 --> 35:18.542
I do not like feeling owned.

35:19.542 --> 35:21.166
It sits real bad on me.

35:29.166 --> 35:30.500
So I'm gonna help you.

35:33.166 --> 35:34.542
I'm gonna help this woman.

35:38.125 --> 35:41.500
Maybe buy a little piece
of my soul back.

35:43.834 --> 35:45.125
What are you doing?

35:45.208 --> 35:46.375
Well, ain't nobody ever certain

35:46.458 --> 35:48.375
what's in half these boxes
to begin with.

35:52.000 --> 35:53.041
(SIGHS)

35:55.208 --> 35:57.667
That's not exactly legal,
Officer Drake.

35:57.750 --> 35:59.333
DRAKE:
No, Mr. Mason, it's not.

35:59.417 --> 36:01.458
But it is something
I can live with.

36:03.667 --> 36:05.041
Are you sure?

36:06.250 --> 36:07.250
Yeah.

36:08.875 --> 36:12.458
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

36:20.917 --> 36:22.375
Look what I just found.

36:35.500 --> 36:37.041
Number 38.

36:42.417 --> 36:44.875
I'd like to see
all articles of incorporation

36:44.959 --> 36:48.583
filed with the State
by the Radiant
Assembly of God, Inc.

36:48.667 --> 36:49.959
For what reason?

36:50.875 --> 36:52.875
I don't have to have a reason.

36:52.959 --> 36:54.208
They're public record.

36:54.291 --> 36:56.709
I have to write something down
for my boss.

36:56.792 --> 36:58.458
I don't care what you tell me.

36:59.625 --> 37:01.291
(SIGHS) Write down...

37:02.041 --> 37:04.375
pertinent curiosity.

37:04.458 --> 37:07.125
Make a right down the hall,
door on the left.

37:07.583 --> 37:08.917
Wait there.

37:09.000 --> 37:10.417
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

37:13.625 --> 37:16.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:29.959 --> 37:33.083
How do, old timer?
You live here long?

37:33.166 --> 37:35.000
Since aught three.

37:35.083 --> 37:36.417
What's it to you?

37:36.500 --> 37:39.166
PETE: I was hoping you
could help me out
with a guy or two.

37:39.250 --> 37:42.166
Marcin Sarecki.
Stayed here back in '14.

37:42.250 --> 37:44.333
During the Ludlow strikes.

37:44.417 --> 37:47.208
-Can't say as I do.
-You sure?

37:47.667 --> 37:50.333
I old. Not daft.

37:51.917 --> 37:53.375
PETE: What about this one?

37:53.834 --> 37:55.208
Stanislaw Nowak.

37:56.166 --> 37:58.959
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:59.041 --> 38:00.166
(SPITS)

38:01.458 --> 38:03.500
That cocksucker I remember.

38:04.583 --> 38:05.834
I guess so.

38:05.917 --> 38:08.583
I reckon
I rightly recall the bastard

38:08.667 --> 38:10.333
that gave me this.

38:10.417 --> 38:12.417
(MUTTERS IN POLISH, SPITS)

38:18.333 --> 38:20.583
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:49.291 --> 38:51.583
Doctor, I ask you
to look at what is marked

38:51.667 --> 38:54.166
as People's Exhibits
19A through H.

38:54.250 --> 38:56.125
Can you tell us what these are?

38:56.208 --> 38:57.667
The photographs I took

38:57.750 --> 39:00.291
before the autopsy
of Charles Dodson.

39:00.375 --> 39:02.792
Now,
as a result of the autopsy,

39:02.875 --> 39:05.542
can you tell us
the cause of death?

39:05.625 --> 39:08.000
Yes. Asphyxiation.

39:08.083 --> 39:10.291
Charles Dodson died as a result
of being deprived

39:10.375 --> 39:11.583
of oxygen to his brain.

39:11.667 --> 39:14.208
BARNES: Yeah. And your autopsy
also indicated that

39:14.291 --> 39:17.625
baby Charlie's eyes
were sewn open with thread.

39:17.709 --> 39:20.792
Can you tell us
if they were sewn open before

39:20.875 --> 39:23.500
-or after his death?
-VIRGIL SHEETS: Yes, I can.

39:23.583 --> 39:27.375
The sewing of the eyelids
was certainly done postmortem.

39:27.458 --> 39:29.792
BARNES: Thank you, Doctor.
No further questions.

39:29.875 --> 39:31.291
(CLEARS THROAT)
Your Honor, I would ask

39:31.375 --> 39:34.041
that the autopsy photographs
be published to the jury.

39:34.125 --> 39:35.458
JUDGE WRIGHT:
So ordered.

39:37.458 --> 39:39.041
-Uh, Dr. Sheets--
-BARNES: Your Honor,

39:39.125 --> 39:42.500
I would ask that the jury
be given the opportunity

39:42.583 --> 39:46.208
to view the photographs
before cross begins.

39:46.291 --> 39:48.041
JUDGE WRIGHT: Of course.
Mr. Mason,

39:48.125 --> 39:50.458
please wait till the jury
has viewed the exhibits.

39:51.291 --> 39:52.333
Right now?

39:53.834 --> 39:55.250
Yes, Mr. Mason.

39:55.625 --> 39:56.625
Now.

40:17.000 --> 40:18.792
(JURY MEMBERS MURMURING)

40:20.291 --> 40:22.083
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Very well.

40:22.166 --> 40:24.083
Thank you,
ladies and gentlemen.

40:24.166 --> 40:25.667
Your witness, Mr. Mason.

40:28.291 --> 40:29.583
MASON: Dr. Sheets,

40:29.667 --> 40:33.750
would you please take a look
at Defense Exhibit number one?

40:33.834 --> 40:35.083
BARNES:
Excuse me, Your Honor,

40:35.166 --> 40:37.834
I'm not exactly sure
what Mr. Mason is referring to.

40:37.917 --> 40:39.333
It's a vouchered piece
of evidence

40:39.417 --> 40:41.417
that was turned over
to the defense
in discovery material.

40:41.500 --> 40:43.083
JUDGE WRIGHT:
I'll allow it.

40:43.166 --> 40:46.667
Let's have the witness identify
the exhibit first, Mr. Barnes.

40:55.000 --> 40:55.959
Oh boy...

40:56.041 --> 40:57.625
MASON: Dr. Sheets,
Would you mind telling us

40:57.709 --> 40:59.542
what it is you're holding
in your hand?

41:00.542 --> 41:03.208
It-- It looks to be a half
of a denture.

41:03.291 --> 41:05.083
Objection!
We did not turn that over!

41:05.166 --> 41:06.583
-Overruled.
-Have you ever seen

41:06.667 --> 41:08.375
the other half
of this denture before?

41:10.458 --> 41:12.000
Um, yes, I have.

41:12.083 --> 41:13.834
MASON: Was that during
an autopsy you conducted

41:13.917 --> 41:16.917
-on George Gannon?
-Objection! Side bar!

41:17.000 --> 41:18.041
Get up here.

41:20.291 --> 41:21.625
What the hell is going on?

41:21.709 --> 41:24.083
I can prove that George Gannon's
suicide was fake.

41:24.166 --> 41:25.041
He was murdered, Judge.

41:25.125 --> 41:26.375
Lower your voice,
we're at side bar.

41:26.458 --> 41:28.333
That's Gannon's denture.
It was recovered in the alleyway

41:28.417 --> 41:31.291
-outside the apartment where--
-Mr. Mason! Lower your voice!

41:31.375 --> 41:33.834
It would prove that someone
other than Emily Dodson
was involved!

41:33.917 --> 41:35.959
In my chambers. Now.

41:36.041 --> 41:38.375
Bailiff, recess the jury!

41:38.458 --> 41:40.166
(GAVEL POUNDS)

41:40.250 --> 41:42.458
(JURY MEMBERS MURMURING)

41:45.792 --> 41:48.417
After Dr. Nance
conducted the official autopsy,

41:48.500 --> 41:50.500
Gannon's body was stolen
from the crematorium

41:50.583 --> 41:52.291
and magically turned up
with a broken hip.

41:52.375 --> 41:54.959
The hip was broken
before the body was stolen,
Your Honor.

41:55.041 --> 41:56.333
You can't prove that!

41:56.417 --> 41:58.041
That's up to the jury,
not you, pal.

41:58.125 --> 41:59.333
A second autopsy on Gannon

41:59.417 --> 42:02.333
would require
a preliminary ruling to admit.

42:02.417 --> 42:05.208
Uh, can-- can--
can I get that ruling now?

42:05.291 --> 42:06.750
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Mm-hm.

42:14.125 --> 42:16.041
I'm not letting you
bring wild theories

42:16.125 --> 42:18.625
before a jury
based on a stolen body.

42:18.709 --> 42:20.709
You don't have a clean chain
of evidence.

42:20.792 --> 42:22.375
-Thank you, Your Honor.
-This is bullshit.

42:22.458 --> 42:24.125
Any reference to this denture

42:24.208 --> 42:26.208
or second autopsy
is inadmissible.

42:26.291 --> 42:27.542
This is fucking rigged,

42:27.625 --> 42:29.917
I have vouchered evidence,
from the DA himself.

42:30.000 --> 42:31.375
-I've ruled on this.
-MASON: Well--

42:31.458 --> 42:34.208
Someone murdered Gannon.
Someone who's still out there.

42:34.291 --> 42:37.208
Someone who-- who stitched
Charlie's fucking eyes open!

42:37.291 --> 42:39.917
And you're as hellbent as he is
on covering this up!

42:40.000 --> 42:42.750
Watch your tone
when speaking to me, Mr. Mason!

42:42.834 --> 42:45.166
Or you will find yourself
held in contempt,

42:45.250 --> 42:48.625
disbarred, and watching me
wipe my hind parts

42:48.709 --> 42:51.250
with your investigator's
license. Now...

42:53.125 --> 42:55.542
recess runs till three.

42:55.625 --> 42:57.417
I assume you'll be ready
to proceed, Mr. Barnes?

42:57.500 --> 42:59.959
Most assuredly, Your Honor.
I plan to call my final witness

43:00.041 --> 43:01.500
-and rest my case.
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Good.

43:02.667 --> 43:03.834
(DOOR OPENS)

43:07.500 --> 43:09.166
(CAR HORN HONKS)

43:13.125 --> 43:15.166
DRAKE: Gonna miss the bus
if we don't hustle.

43:22.333 --> 43:24.458
Just trying to get you there
is all.

43:35.333 --> 43:37.792
You tell your aunt,
I'm paying the phone bill,

43:37.875 --> 43:39.625
so any amount of calls
is all right.

43:39.709 --> 43:42.542
I don't want her worryin',
or worryin' you.

43:45.083 --> 43:46.417
CABBIE:
Afternoon, ma'am.

43:54.000 --> 43:55.625
This is some bad business.

43:55.709 --> 43:57.333
No. No, no.
It ain't bad business.

43:57.417 --> 44:00.125
I just need to help
this lady out is all.

44:00.208 --> 44:02.417
-I need you and this little one
out of reach...
-(SIGHS)

44:02.500 --> 44:03.917
...while I fix it right.

44:05.125 --> 44:07.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:13.250 --> 44:14.667
Here you go.

44:31.125 --> 44:34.458
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(ELEVATOR DINGS)

44:40.250 --> 44:42.458
(GROANS)

44:43.500 --> 44:45.083
(SIGHS)

44:45.166 --> 44:46.458
There you are!

44:46.542 --> 44:48.208
I was about to storm
the men's room

44:48.291 --> 44:49.917
when the bailiff
ratted you out.

44:50.000 --> 44:51.166
-Not now.
-Yes, now.

44:51.250 --> 44:53.375
Wait till you see
what I got you.

44:53.458 --> 44:56.000
Thirty-Six Del Pio Drive.

44:56.083 --> 44:57.792
They're not putting
Ennis on the stand.

44:57.875 --> 44:59.500
And they gave me 15 minutes

44:59.583 --> 45:01.542
to prepare
for this fucking jail matron.

45:01.625 --> 45:03.083
I found J.H.

45:04.333 --> 45:06.917
Woodland Acres.
It's a church subsidiary.

45:07.000 --> 45:08.959
A real estate development
out in the sticks.

45:09.041 --> 45:10.208
Jim Hicks set it up,

45:10.291 --> 45:12.291
and Herman Baggerly
is named as chairman.

45:13.250 --> 45:14.542
-Baggerly?
-Yeah.

45:14.625 --> 45:16.542
Then I went across Spring Street
to the County Assessor's Office

45:16.625 --> 45:18.417
and started pulling titles
and deeds.

45:18.500 --> 45:22.834
It's a place called Girard,
incorporated in 1927,

45:22.917 --> 45:24.333
and they only sold 11 plots,

45:24.417 --> 45:27.125
and guess who owns one
for next to nothing?

45:28.125 --> 45:31.375
-You stole a title?
-You stole a body.

45:31.458 --> 45:32.959
Look at the signature.

45:37.917 --> 45:39.792
Big "J," skinny "H."

45:39.875 --> 45:42.500
Thirty-Six Del Pio Drive.
Twenty acres for a dollar?

45:42.583 --> 45:45.375
It's a hell of a deal
for a former accountant.

45:45.458 --> 45:47.250
I could kiss you,
Della Street.

45:47.333 --> 45:48.333
Please don't.

45:48.417 --> 45:49.500
-BAILIFF: Mr. Mason?
-Yeah.

45:49.583 --> 45:50.875
BAILIFF:
We're heading back, counselor.

45:50.959 --> 45:52.000
MASON: Thank you.

45:52.875 --> 45:55.333
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

45:58.667 --> 46:00.250
PETE: That old Polack
spits all over me,

46:00.333 --> 46:01.375
tells me to come to see you.

46:01.458 --> 46:03.667
I'm surprised
he didn't take a poke at you.

46:03.750 --> 46:05.000
Those old bastards

46:05.083 --> 46:08.000
got a real burr in their saddle
about that whole Ludlow mess.

46:08.083 --> 46:10.542
Well, fortunately,
he could barely spit.

46:11.500 --> 46:13.959
No Sarecki.
No Nowak.

46:14.041 --> 46:15.417
Who'd you say
the other one was?

46:15.500 --> 46:17.750
Ennis.
Worked as a Pinkerton.

46:17.834 --> 46:19.333
BETTY: Ennis.
With an E?

46:19.417 --> 46:20.750
E-N-N-I-S.

46:20.834 --> 46:22.834
Very close to "penis."

46:23.875 --> 46:25.542
Never thought
about it like that.

46:25.625 --> 46:28.542
Pinkertons, thugs, miners,
that's one thing.

46:28.625 --> 46:30.500
It's a fair enough fight.

46:30.583 --> 46:34.625
But when the army came in
shooting, mm-mm.

46:34.709 --> 46:37.542
Sweet Jesus wept-- Shit.

46:37.625 --> 46:39.083
No Ennis, either.

46:39.166 --> 46:41.583
You sure?
He's got to be there.

46:41.667 --> 46:42.917
That's where you look.

46:43.000 --> 46:44.959
And you just saw me
fucking look.

46:45.041 --> 46:47.834
Most likely we paid
the thugs in cash

46:47.917 --> 46:49.542
and the Pinkies as a group.

46:51.208 --> 46:53.458
How about the fella
who was doling out the dollars?

46:53.542 --> 46:55.291
Any chance he's still around?

46:55.375 --> 46:56.875
-From back then?
-Yeah.

46:56.959 --> 46:58.333
Dog-fuck if I know.

46:59.959 --> 47:03.291
Hope you don't mind me saying,
but you got a colorful way
with words.

47:03.375 --> 47:05.750
BETTY: You're not a goddamn
Papist, are you?

47:06.542 --> 47:07.750
Here we go.

47:08.375 --> 47:11.625
Accounting, 1914.

47:11.709 --> 47:14.458
Furthest thing from it.
Episcopalian.

47:14.542 --> 47:17.083
Hmm, I don't like them much
either.

47:18.250 --> 47:20.125
Dead. Don't know.

47:20.208 --> 47:21.625
Don't know. Dead.

47:21.709 --> 47:22.917
That say "Seidel"?

47:24.291 --> 47:26.458
-"Eric Q. Seidel"?
-Him.

47:26.542 --> 47:29.875
He became vice president.
Top row, second from the left.

47:31.500 --> 47:34.458
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

47:35.333 --> 47:36.417
Betty...

47:37.417 --> 47:39.458
can I buy you a drink?

47:39.542 --> 47:42.000
BAILIFF: Do you swear that
the testimony you shall give

47:42.083 --> 47:43.875
shall be the truth,
the whole truth,

47:43.959 --> 47:45.834
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

47:45.917 --> 47:46.917
I do.

47:50.125 --> 47:52.875
Please state your name
and occupation for the record.

47:52.959 --> 47:54.583
My name is Barbara Fry,

47:54.667 --> 47:56.458
and I am the matron
at the City Jail.

47:56.542 --> 47:58.959
And were you responsible
for the supervision

47:59.041 --> 48:02.083
of the defendant, Emily Dodson,
on or about January 5th?

48:02.166 --> 48:03.208
Yes, I was.

48:03.291 --> 48:05.959
Did anything of note
happen on that date?

48:06.041 --> 48:08.458
She had a visit
from Sister Alice McKeegan.

48:08.542 --> 48:11.542
And were you present
for the entirety of that visit?

48:11.625 --> 48:12.709
BARBARA FRY:
I was.

48:12.792 --> 48:14.625
Please tell the jury
what you heard.

48:14.709 --> 48:17.375
Uh, objection! Uh,
conversation between Emily

48:17.458 --> 48:19.500
and her spiritual advisor
is privileged.

48:19.583 --> 48:21.875
Sit down, Mr. Mason.
That privilege is broken

48:21.959 --> 48:24.291
if a third party is present.

48:24.375 --> 48:26.542
BARNES:
You may answer the question.

48:26.625 --> 48:29.583
BARBARA: Emily said that if
she had not been with George,

48:29.667 --> 48:32.166
-Charlie'd still be alive.
-Continue.

48:32.250 --> 48:34.875
Then she said,
"I killed my baby."

48:34.959 --> 48:37.709
-No! That's not--
-Control your client, Mr. Mason!

48:37.792 --> 48:39.542
That is--
That is not what I said!

48:39.625 --> 48:40.917
Jesus, she's twisting it.

48:41.000 --> 48:42.792
-Do-- Do something.
-BARBARA:
Then the Sister asked her

48:42.875 --> 48:46.208
if she had pressed a pillow
over her baby's mouth

48:46.291 --> 48:48.625
and stitched his eyes open.

48:48.709 --> 48:51.291
-And the defendant's response?
-Objection!

48:51.375 --> 48:54.959
The defendant nodded
and said, "Yes."

48:55.041 --> 48:56.583
That is a lie!

48:56.667 --> 48:59.917
-Sit down, Mrs. Dodson,
or I'll have you removed!
-Stop lying! She's lying!

49:00.000 --> 49:01.333
-She's lying!
-MASON: I know.

49:01.417 --> 49:03.583
Your Honor, given
this overheard confession,

49:03.667 --> 49:06.583
I ask, no, demand,
that I be allowed to argue

49:06.667 --> 49:09.250
in summation that the defendant
Emily Dodson

49:09.333 --> 49:11.709
not only conspired to kidnap,
but in fact,

49:11.792 --> 49:13.166
murdered her child!

49:13.250 --> 49:15.041
-(GALLERY CLAMORING)
-I didn't do it! I didn't do it!

49:15.125 --> 49:17.333
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Order!
-I didn't do it!

49:17.417 --> 49:19.875
-JUDGE WRIGHT: Order!
-The Prosecution rests.

49:19.959 --> 49:20.959
JUDGE WRIGHT: Order!

49:21.041 --> 49:23.458
-(GAVEL POUNDING)
-(ALL SHOUTING)

49:23.542 --> 49:25.041
JUDGE WRIGHT:
Order!

49:28.000 --> 49:29.291
REPORTER 1:
Hey, there they are!

49:29.375 --> 49:30.709
MAN 1: Murderer!

49:30.792 --> 49:33.000
(CROWD CLAMORING)

49:33.083 --> 49:35.083
REPORTER 2: Mr. Mason,
is there any comment on that?

49:35.166 --> 49:36.792
The woman perjured herself.

49:36.875 --> 49:38.333
They don't have a case,
so they lie.

49:38.417 --> 49:40.166
That's how low the DA goes.

49:40.250 --> 49:42.834
(INAUDIBLE)

49:46.208 --> 49:48.083
You want a story?
Ask him why he didn't call

49:48.166 --> 49:49.875
the first detective
on the scene.

49:49.959 --> 49:51.083
Take her home.

49:51.166 --> 49:54.792
(INDISTINCT CLAMOR)

49:58.875 --> 50:01.792
(REPORTERS SHOUTING)

50:03.834 --> 50:05.625
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

50:06.500 --> 50:08.208
MAN 2: Repent or die, whore!

50:08.291 --> 50:10.417
I can't believe
that woman lied.

50:11.250 --> 50:13.625
After what she let happen
to you.

50:14.583 --> 50:16.083
Take a runner!

50:17.125 --> 50:19.291
It's okay.
It's okay.

50:19.375 --> 50:21.834
None of them matters, Della.

50:21.917 --> 50:24.750
Don't give up hope.
Okay?

50:24.834 --> 50:26.333
It's our turn next.

50:26.417 --> 50:29.083
No. Mr. Barnes is gonna drop
the charges.

50:30.750 --> 50:33.750
Once Sister Alice brings
Charlie back, he'll be alive.

50:36.458 --> 50:38.542
It can't be murder
if he's alive.

50:38.625 --> 50:39.834
(WOMAN YELLING)

50:41.625 --> 50:43.291
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

50:48.792 --> 50:50.959
How do you think that went,
E.B.?

50:53.083 --> 50:57.834
(IMITATES E.B.) Well, I have
a few observations, boy-o.

51:03.375 --> 51:04.625
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

51:08.375 --> 51:10.500
-Hey, Gene!
-HOLCOMB: Hey, Ellie.

51:10.583 --> 51:12.542
Is, uh, your better half around?

51:12.625 --> 51:14.375
Back in the garage
with his one true love.

51:14.458 --> 51:15.709
Do you want to come in
for coffee?

51:15.792 --> 51:17.250
No, thanks.
Uh, not today.

51:17.333 --> 51:19.458
It's... work.

51:19.542 --> 51:22.959
(CHILDREN CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY)

51:27.125 --> 51:28.834
Where the fuck have you been?

51:31.709 --> 51:34.583
I didn't think I was needed.
Wasn't asked to testify.

51:34.667 --> 51:37.250
Fucking Barnes ices me out,
for what, I don't know.

51:37.333 --> 51:38.500
HOLCOMB:
You know what.

51:39.834 --> 51:41.083
That bullshit with McGuire?

51:41.166 --> 51:42.417
Like you haven't done
the same thing.

51:42.500 --> 51:44.875
-Barnes knows you're lying.
-ENNIS: Of course I'm lying.

51:44.959 --> 51:47.041
What am I supposed
to say to the DA?

51:47.125 --> 51:49.208
That I'm getting soused
at the Elks club

51:49.291 --> 51:50.458
when Charlie turns up?

51:50.542 --> 51:52.333
Well, makes more sense
than what you told him or me.

51:52.417 --> 51:54.458
ENNIS:
Huge case drops in my lap,

51:54.542 --> 51:57.709
I'm gonna grab it, yeah?
I got mouths to feed.

51:57.792 --> 52:00.417
Case like this could move us
both up the ladder.

52:00.500 --> 52:01.792
HOLCOMB: Bullshit!

52:01.875 --> 52:04.583
You jumped Royce so we could
run the crime scene.

52:04.667 --> 52:05.709
No, Gene.

52:06.583 --> 52:08.000
You ran the scene.

52:08.875 --> 52:10.667
I was your second.

52:10.750 --> 52:12.625
You told me what to do.

52:12.709 --> 52:14.500
I followed your lead.

52:14.583 --> 52:17.333
And forget about Mason.
He can't prove a thing.

52:17.417 --> 52:19.750
If Barnes wasn't such
a fucking chickenshit--

52:19.834 --> 52:22.333
Nice looking car, Joe. (GRUNTS)

52:22.417 --> 52:26.208
You love this car? Huh?
It's important to you? Huh?

52:26.291 --> 52:29.625
-(GLASS CRACKLES)
-What about Ellie? The kids?

52:29.709 --> 52:32.458
Huh? Or me?
Your goddamn partner!

52:32.542 --> 52:33.667
(METAL THUDS)

52:34.959 --> 52:36.333
Just how dirty are you, Joe?

52:36.417 --> 52:39.667
I need to know.
Right fucking now.

52:39.750 --> 52:42.291
You brought me into this racket.

52:42.375 --> 52:44.500
You tied me in
with the Lucky Lagoon,

52:44.583 --> 52:46.750
the whores at Jin's,
the kickbacks.

52:46.834 --> 52:48.458
That ain't the same thing.

52:48.542 --> 52:50.750
Sarecki, Nowak, Gannon.

52:50.834 --> 52:52.583
Did you kill 'em all, Joe?

52:53.583 --> 52:55.792
(PANTING)
Did you stitch that baby up?

52:57.375 --> 52:59.417
I got hired to do a thing.

53:00.667 --> 53:03.709
That thing went a little off.

53:04.125 --> 53:05.625
(SIGHS)

53:08.083 --> 53:10.250
Who else can finger you
for this?

53:10.333 --> 53:12.417
-Really wanna know?
-HOLCOMB: No.

53:14.125 --> 53:15.417
I want 'em dead.

53:17.208 --> 53:19.083
MASON: (IMITATING E.B.)
See, a good lawyer,

53:19.166 --> 53:20.500
an actual lawyer,

53:20.583 --> 53:22.667
never would have promised
to get the client off,

53:22.750 --> 53:23.875
to find the killer.

53:23.959 --> 53:25.709
Shouldn't prosecute
from the defense table.

53:25.792 --> 53:28.208
You can't prosecute
from the defense table.

53:28.291 --> 53:30.709
And yet here we are,
driving to God knows where

53:30.792 --> 53:33.709
for God knows whatever reason,
when a real lawyer,

53:33.792 --> 53:36.417
an actual lawyer,
would have done what?

53:36.500 --> 53:38.542
Would have stuffed a towel
under the door

53:38.625 --> 53:40.667
and turned on
the fucking gas?

53:40.750 --> 53:43.875
How the fuck is that
working out for you, E.B.?

53:43.959 --> 53:46.375
They got Brandy Alexanders
and cigar girls

53:46.458 --> 53:48.625
in good lawyer purgatory?

53:48.709 --> 53:50.041
'Cause guess what?

53:50.125 --> 53:53.291
You should be here,
doing your fucking job,

53:53.375 --> 53:55.125
you fucking coward!

53:55.834 --> 53:57.000
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

53:57.083 --> 53:59.166
(BANGING)

54:04.834 --> 54:05.834
(SIGHS)

54:32.750 --> 54:36.291
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

55:00.709 --> 55:02.709
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

55:05.041 --> 55:07.917
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

55:34.583 --> 55:36.250
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

55:43.917 --> 55:45.625
-JIM HICKS: Hello.
-MASON: Uh, hi.

55:45.709 --> 55:48.917
Um, I'm sorry to bother you.
I'm looking for Jim Hicks?

55:51.792 --> 55:54.083
You're that Dodson girl's
lawyer?

55:54.166 --> 55:55.917
Seen your picture
in the newspaper.

55:56.583 --> 55:57.709
Yeah, I...

55:59.083 --> 56:00.917
I've been waiting for you
to find me.

56:14.542 --> 56:18.500
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

57:59.875 --> 58:01.875
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

58:05.709 --> 58:06.625
♪ (SLOW MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

58:06.709 --> 58:09.041
WOMAN: (WHISPERS) Alice. Alice.

58:09.291 --> 58:10.834
(SCREAMS) Alice!

58:11.875 --> 58:13.208
Something on your mind,
daughter?

58:13.291 --> 58:15.250
Just wondering what the Lord
has in store.

58:16.917 --> 58:20.083
Mr. Hicks, was George Gannon
stealing from the church?

58:20.291 --> 58:21.875
The church was stealing from
the church.

58:24.875 --> 58:26.125
Wanna look at what I found?

58:27.583 --> 58:28.458
What?

58:29.709 --> 58:31.125
PERRY MASON:
I've got to talk to Emily.

58:31.208 --> 58:32.500
She won't hear a word you say.

58:32.583 --> 58:35.458
Come this Sunday, Mr. Mason,
everyone in this city

58:35.709 --> 58:37.458
will beg me to forgive them.

58:39.166 --> 58:40.583
What kind of man are you,
Mr. Mason?

58:42.083 --> 58:45.375
I am fighting
for a woman's life!

58:48.291 --> 58:49.417
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
